The Ebonyi State Governor, Chief David Umahi has ordered the immediate closure of gas stations and outlets in the State to forestall possible outbreak of fire in the dry season. In a statement signed by the Special Assistant to the Governor on Media, Mr. Francis Nweze said that the direct among other things was also to ensure that Health Safety and Environment regulation of Ebonyi State conform to National and International best oil and gas field practice. According to the statement which reads, “the Governor has directed immediate shutdown of all illegal gas stations and outlets in the State”. “To this end, all gas stations and outlets must operate with the approval of the Ebonyi State Capital Territory Development Board (ACTDB) and Department of Petroleum Resources, (DPR). The Governor also warned that defaulters of the directive will be penalized in accordance with the laws of the state and shall pay approved penalties. He further directed all the relevant authorities to ensure that all concerned abide strictly to the directive. It would be recalled that since the dry season which is usually occasioned by incessant fire outbreaks, there has been pockets of fire outbreaks in the state capital. The State government had last year also shut down some gas station that are situated very close to residential homes describing such station as time bomb waiting to explode. But regrettably, few months after the closure, the gas stations commenced operation thereby forcing some residents to call for permanent shutdown of the gas stations or on the alternative have them relocate to non-residential areas.